						               													<description>You were born in Fantastate, a small borderland between the Realm of Fantasy in the north and the Real World in the south. You feel that beyond the frontier of your village there is something more. A world full of Treasures, Monsters, Spells and heroic deeds. You simply cannot withstand the desire for adventure. Thus prepare for your Journey! The local Smithy can make you any weapon you wish, you just need to express yourself clearly. What about a War-Broom, or a Sharpened Needle? Then you can hire an escort in the Tavern. Care for a crazy Squirrel? And now you are ready to go! Fantastate interestingly combines a game with words and letters with a role-playing game (RPG). The game also offers 4 types of play with each of them having its own specific rules and giving you unmatched and different experiences &amp;ndash; see below.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Action &amp;ndash; each against each in a humorous nature for 3 - 6 players, 60 &amp;ndash; 90 min.&amp;#10;Cooperative &amp;ndash; all against the game (Monsters) for 2 &amp;ndash; 6 players, 60 &amp;ndash; 90 min.&amp;#10;Deathmatch &amp;ndash; each against each, but now really really serious for 2 &amp;ndash; 6 players, 50 &amp;ndash; 70 min.&amp;#10;Team Play &amp;ndash; action game in teams for 6 &amp;ndash; 12 players, 60 &amp;ndash; 120 min.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game contents:&amp;#10;6 big Hero cards&amp;#10;6 Hero Pawns&amp;#10;75 Letter tiles (Cze, Eng, Ger)&amp;#10;2 Dice and 1 Sticker sheet&amp;#10;54 Location cards&amp;#10;24 Spell, Weapon, Friend and Vehicle cards&amp;#10;50 Golden counters - money&amp;#10;30 Orange counters - points&amp;#10;A comprehensible Guide for the 4 Game Variants in Czech and English&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
